            is permanent. In our earlier theoretical model, these two parts correspond to the two price effects engendered by the initial impact of λZ. The transitory part in that model corresponds to an intraday risk premium (in the spirit of Spiegel and Subrahmanyam1995), whereas the permanent part is that which remains even after dealer inventories are shared marketwide (i.e.,
